+# Dashboard Truth Contract
+
+Pala OS v6 dashboard is a court surface. It must render current evidence state, not optimism.
+
+## Status Rules
+
+- Unknown external or runtime state returns `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON`.
+- Missing evidence returns `PARTIAL`.
+- Missing owner approval returns `RELEASE_BLOCKED`.
+- Docker daemon absence means Docker Boot cannot return `PASS`.
+- Source Court `PARTIAL` keeps the Source Court panel `PARTIAL`.
+- Legacy archive data can appear only through sanitized Source Court summary.
+- Raw `legacy/**` file lists must not be exposed in dashboard state.
+- Token economy estimates must be marked `estimated`.
+- Overall dashboard status must never be greener than the riskiest child panel.
+
+## Panel Truth Table
+
+| Panel | Data Source | Evidence Source | Fallback State | PASS Condition | Truth Risk |
+|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Overview | `buildAppState.summary`, `court`, `sourceStampGate` | SQLite evidence counts, source cards, ledger, court | `RELEASE_BLOCKED` | Court not release-blocked, source gate `PASS`, ledger has evidence | Overview can hide downstream blockers if greener than child panels |
+| Mission Control | `route`, `nextActions`, `jobRuns`, `runs` | SQLite `command_runs` and `job_runs` | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | Mission/run ledger proves active mission state and no blocking court state | Route text can look decisive without mission evidence |
+| CI Court | GitHub bridge and audit state | GitHub CLI/API readback and workflow runs | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | GitHub governance readback and required checks are proven | CI green without branch protection/review can fake governance |
+| Evidence Center | `ledger`, `sourceCards`, `evidenceSprint` | SQLite ledger records and source-card table | `PARTIAL` | Ledger has records and source cards exist | Empty evidence must never display `PASS` |
+| Source Court | `sanitizeSourceCourtAudit(buildSourceCourtAudit())` | Source Court summary and `sourceStampGate` | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | `sourceStampGate` is `PASS` with no release-blocking source-chain gaps | Raw legacy/source files must not leak into dashboard state |
+| Skill Registry | Seed skill registry | `skills/registry/seed-skills.json` | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | Seed registry loads and legacy registry is not default-loaded | Legacy skill index must not become active skills |
+| MCP Health | MCP registry and stdio proof | MCP health CLI/test output | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | Live MCP health proof is attached to dashboard state | Registry presence is not live MCP health |
+| Docker Boot | Latest `.pala/evidence/docker` smoke JSON | Docker version, compose config/build/up/health/down evidence | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | Docker daemon available, compose build/up succeeds, API health passes, compose down succeeds | Compose config alone is not runtime proof |
+| Benchmark Radar | `benchmark/benchmark-state.json` | Benchmark categories and evidence counts | `NOT_AVAILABLE_WITH_REASON` | Fixture-backed benchmark suite has no blocked category | Placeholder benchmarks can look like proof |
+| Token Economy | `tokenBudget` and `tokenSnapshots` | SQLite token snapshots or deterministic estimate | `PARTIAL` | Measured token accounting exists with confidence metadata | Estimates can be mistaken for measured savings |
+| Release Court | `evaluateCourt()` | Owner approval, required standards, source cards, ledger, source gate | `RELEASE_BLOCKED` | Owner approval present and no release blockers remain | Release must never turn green without owner approval |
+
+## API Contract
+
+`/api/state` must include `dashboardTruthContract` with:
+
+- `status`
+- `rules`
+- `summary`
+- `panels`
+
+Each panel entry must include:
+
+- `id`
+- `panel`
+- `status`
+- `dataSource`
+- `evidenceSource`
+- `fallbackState`
+- `passCondition`
+- `truthRisk`
+- `statusMapping`
+- `evidencePresent`
+- `estimated`
+
+## Court Rule
+
+Dashboard truth is not release approval. A truthful dashboard can show working subsystems while the release remains `RELEASE_BLOCKED`.
